=\u0022kqgk38fm3xeuv8opppcx.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022450\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/s--m25QuRH5--/c_scale,f_auto,fl_progressive,q_80,w_800/kqgk38fm3xeuv8opppcx.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022kpvpapyww92kcd2rkuj7.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/t_original/kpvpapyww92kcd2rkuj7.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-12T15:41:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223397975\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175833\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528812039\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022kqgk38fm3xeuv8opppcx.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022450\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/s--m25QuRH5--/c_scale,f_auto,fl_progressive,q_80,w_800/kqgk38fm3xeuv8opppcx.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan\u0027t they afford to hire someone who can do a good photoshop? Look at how those wheels are clipping into the ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-12T15:48:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223398033\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175833\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528818080\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLook at how those wheels are clipping into the ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd at something looking like a white building reflected in the solar panels.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait...\u003Cbr\u003E\nOh, ....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GDJ","CreatedById":58462,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-12T22:37:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223398033\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175833\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528818080\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan\u0027t they afford to hire someone who can do a good photoshop? Look at how those wheels are clipping into the ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223398037\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175833\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528818490\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd at something looking like a white building reflected in the solar panels.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait...\u003Cbr\u003E\nOh, ....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDreadful work I agree.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-12T22:45:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223398033\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175833\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528818080\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan\u0027t they afford to hire someone who can do a good photoshop? Look at how those wheels are clipping into the ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hate it when i stand on sand and my feet clip into the ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Girl%20Standing%20in%20Wet%20Beach%20San\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022332\u0022 src=\u0022https://s3.envato.com/files/65059068/Girl%20Standing%20in%20Wet%20Beach%20Sand%20preview%20image.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022590\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Bury-your-Head-in-the-sand_new.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022464\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.foxvalleysafety.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Bury-your-Head-in-the-sand_new.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen was that render made, 2003? 2004?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003Eoff topic\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-13T04:25:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*ahem* back on topic!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think opportunity will be just fine.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-13T06:44:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think opportunity will have to stay idle for quite a long time so breezes can blow some of the dust off. The dust on it is without a doubt extremely light, and i\u00A0think even the most martian of breezes can blow it off. But we will have to see.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-13T06:59:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust for 50 USD more... What a shame.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.ebay.com/bhp/wiper-blades\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.ebay.com/bhp/wiper-blades\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"insert_name","CreatedById":150339,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-13T08:09:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-to-hold-media-teleconference-on-martian-dust-storm-mars-opportunity-rover\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-to-hold-media-teleconference-on-martian-dust-storm-mars-opportunity-rover\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t sound too good\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-13T16:16:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3156735791\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/SGuzewich/status/1006701616278458375\u0022 style=\u0022height:367px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-13T17:17:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPress conf live in under 15 minutes:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/fIKxdRFx2Wo?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022459\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-13T17:39:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPower savings has to be balanced with operations, since operations keep the rover warm. Sleep mode for an extended period could be mission ending.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nNonetheless, the temp is coming into summer temps, and the storm has warmed the atmosphere, so they think it can weather storm.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nIf they lose all battery power, it goes into clock fault mode, and the rover with then try contact at intervals (not knowing what time it is) at times when it has power.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-13T17:52:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7213072654\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/jeff_foust/status/1006957202492542978\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Diche Bach","CreatedById":76097,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-14T00:46:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, to you guys who are buffs or experts on this stuff: why did they send rovers to Mars without a radioisotope generator? That tech is like what . . . 45 year old? Was it just cost?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt seems it was always pretty obvious Mars is a dusty place, and thus solar power was problematic\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022800px-Curiosity_Self-Portrait_at_\u0027Big_Sk\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Curiosity_Self-Portrait_at_\u0027Big_Sky\u0027_Drilling_Site.jpg/800px-Curiosity_Self-Portrait_at_\u0027Big_Sky\u0027_Drilling_Site.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022557\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-14T01:22:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRTGs are expensive and the specific isotope of plutonium for them is in short supply. Production has restarted, but it\u2019s on the order of grams/year\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VaPaL","CreatedById":150974,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-14T01:39:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe also mass/size. Curiosity is a lot bigger than Opportunity and all \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E I ever saw in photos were big (but I never looked much into it)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022EFNmIx9NxFoM75lXb6SJlzSzW3AvPllEsettaqkR0r4.jpg?s=6d68d45a4e12fe526b53f6f95971397f\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.redditmedia.com/EFNmIx9NxFoM75lXb6SJlzSzW3AvPllEsettaqkR0r4.jpg?s=6d68d45a4e12fe526b53f6f95971397f\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Image result for Radioisotope thermoelectric generator\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.zmescience.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/011053vsdb8drh81d9s99r.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Image result for Radioisotope thermoelectric generator\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/RTG_radiation_measurement.jpg/403px-RTG_radiation_measurement.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: this one from Apollo 14 ALSEP looks smaller, but it\u0027s hard to say in terms of power generation:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b5/ALSEP_Apollo_14_RTG.jpg/1024px-ALSEP_Apollo_14_RTG.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00221024px-ALSEP_Apollo_14_RTG.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022File:SNAP 8DR core asembly.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a6/SNAP_8DR_core_asembly.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-06-14T01:41:55Z\u0022 title=\u002206/14/2018 01:41  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJune 14, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by VaPaL\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-14T02:47:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpirit and Opportunity were not designed for long life, they were expected to operate for 90 days.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n90 days... We\u0027re now on Sol 5107?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf Opportunity was a Kerbal, badS = True.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-14T03:16:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223398892\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175833\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528937179\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002276097\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Diche Bach\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Diche Bach said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhy\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E did they send rovers to Mars without a radioisotope generator?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHeavy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, will not look good if broken (think Beagle).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-14T04:03:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot even \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u003Cbr\u003E\nWhy does this fully mechanised rover not have a simple windshield\u00A0wiper.\u003Cbr\u003E\nOr can\u0027t fold-unfold its unfoldable solar panels to shake off the dust.\u003Cbr\u003E\nWasn\u0027t it sent to a dusty desert?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-14T06:42:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223398963\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175833\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528949001\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy does this fully mechanised rover not have a simple windshield\u00A0wiper.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlready answered two posts above yours:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was designed to operate for 90 days. Long-term maintenance gear was considered pointless.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-14T07:13:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich begs the question, why is such complex and expensive hardware expected to last only a few months, while the total mission time from concept and design to data analysis takes many years. I think that both Spirit and Opportunity showed us that there is plenty of science to be done well past the designed lifetime.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomehow I believe that such expensive projects should be built with as many safeguards as possible for indefinite extension of operation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis existing approach stinks of planned obsolescence.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}